No. ! (of 4) Baldwin steam tram is in the Powerhouse Museum.  There were four steam trams imported from the USA to take visitors from Redfern railway station to the Sydney Intenational Exhibition at the Garden Palace.

See - <a href="http://www.powerhousemuseum.com/collection/database/?irn=214923&amp;search=baldwin+steam&amp;images=&amp;c=&amp;s=" rel="nofollow">www.powerhousemuseum.com/collection/database/?irn=214923&...</a>

&quot; The first trial of the steam motors was on 23 September 1879. Six days later one steam tram was put into service and on 29 September all four motors were in operation. &quot;
